MerizoDB README

Welcome to MerizoDB!

COMPONENTS

  merizod - The database server.
  merizos - Sharding router.
  merizo  - The database shell (uses interactive javascript).

UTILITIES

  merizodump         - Create a binary dump of the contents of a database.
  merizorestore      - Restore data from the output created by merizodump.
  merizoexport       - Export the contents of a collection to JSON or CSV.
  merizoimport       - Import data from JSON, CSV or TSV.
  merizofiles        - Put, get and delete files from GridFS.
  merizostat         - Show the status of a running merizod/merizos.
  bsondump          - Convert BSON files into human-readable formats.
  merizoreplay       - Traffic capture and replay tool.
  merizotop          - Track time spent reading and writing data.
  install_compass   - Installs MerizoDB Compass for your platform.

BUILDING

  See docs/building.md.

RUNNING

  For command line options invoke:

    $ ./merizod --help

  To run a single server database:

    $ sudo mkdir -p /data/db
    $ ./merizod
    $
    $ # The merizo javascript shell connects to localhost and test database by default:
    $ ./merizo
    > help

INSTALLING COMPASS

  You can install compass using the install_compass script packaged with MerizoDB:

    $ ./install_compass

  This will download the appropriate MerizoDB Compass package for your platform
  and install it.

DRIVERS

  Client drivers for most programming languages are available at
  https://docs.merizodb.com/manual/applications/drivers/. Use the shell
  ("merizo") for administrative tasks.

BUG REPORTS

  See https://github.com/merizodb/merizo/wiki/Submit-Bug-Reports.

PACKAGING

  Packages are created dynamically by the package.py script located in the
  buildscripts directory. This will generate RPM and Debian packages.

